author: Pedro Villa y Caña
title: "Cerramos bien febrero": AMLO celebra inauguración de acueductos, tramo del Tren Maya y compra de plantas a Iberdrola | El Universal
text:
Por la inauguración de diversas obras en este mes, como acueductos, un rompeolas, un museo, el cierre de la compra de 13 plantas de energía eléctrica a Iberdrola y la inauguración de un tramo más del Tren Maya , el presidente Andrés Manuel López Obrador celebró que en su gobierno “cerramos bien febrero”. En sus redes sociales, el jefe del Ejecutivo federal recordó que el viernes pasado inauguró los acueductos de Guadalajara y Concordia, Sinaloa; el sábado nacionalizó la salinera de Guerrero Negro, Baja California Sur; y el domingo inauguró 450 kilómetros de acueductos para los pueblos yaquis en Sonora.
El lunes pasado, destacó, inauguró mil 600 metros del Rompeolas de Salina Cruz, Oaxaca.
Lee también Vías del Tren Maya traen desarrollo y prosperidad de norte a sur en Quintana Roo: Mara Lezama
“El martes llegamos en el tren Insurgente de Zinacantepec a Santa Fe. Ese mismo día en Tamazunchale se compraron a Iberdrola 13 plantas de ciclo combinado para recuperar la soberanía de la industria eléctrica nacional”, señaló.
Ayer, el presidente Lopez Obrador viajó en el Tren Maya desde Palenque hasta Cancún, y luego inauguró el Gran Museo de Chichén Itzá.
Destacó que hoy, junto con su gabinete legal y ampliado, inauguró el tramo del Tren Maya que corre de Cancún a Playa del Carmen, incluida la estación de Puerto Morelos.
“Como Quijotes: Lo difícil lo logramos porque luchar por la transformación de México es siempre caminar en pos de una bella utopía”, escribió.
Cerramos bien febrero:
El viernes inauguramos los acueductos de Guadalajara y Concordia, Sinaloa.
El sábado nacionalizamos la salinera de Guerrero Negro, Baja California Sur.
El domingo inauguramos 450 kilómetros de acueductos para los pueblos yaquis en Sonora.

title: Ballot tampering investigation in Glacier County raises election integrity concerns | Montana Politics | montanarightnow.com
text:
GLACIER COUNTY, Mont. – An investigation is underway after a video emerged showing a man tampering with a ballot box in Browning on the Blackfeet Reservation. This incident is stirring concerns about election integrity in Montana, especially amid a significant race for U.S. Senate.
The video, obtained by Fox News Digital, captures the man, Laszlo Gendler, at the ballot box located at the Glacier County Satellite Office. This is one of the two designated boxes in the county.
Montana is currently a focus due to the hotly contested senate race between Jon Tester and Tim Sheehy.
Fox News reported that Gendler was employed by the Democratic Senatorial Campaign Committee (DSCC). Gendler reportedly informed the Glacier County Election Administrator that he was sent to test the box's security. The video shows him tugging on the box before leaving.
The DSCC responded to Fox News, clarifying that Gendler's actions were not aligned with their procedures. "Out of an abundance of caution, they're no longer doing this type of work moving forward," they stated.
The investigation continues as the state looks into ensuring the security and integrity of its election process.

author: Brigid Brown
title: Prince William gets cheeky with Charles during Coronation rehearsal and the moment is goin | Royal | News | Express.co.uk
text:
Queen Camilla's sister tears up on Coronation Day
Prince William practising his Coronation vow with King Charles III is going viral on social media.
It has emerged after the release of Charles III: The Coronation Year on Boxing Day.
William is meant to pledge his allegiance to his father and then kiss him on the cheek. During the rehearsal, William bends down and kisses Charles on the right side of his face, but it seems like Charles isn’t quite satisfied.
William then asks, “Oh, is it the left side?” before adding, “Your left cheek is better!”. He obliges, giving his father a second peck.
The moment has caught fans’ attention with the clip already amassing half a million views, 20,000 likes and 200 comments over at TikTok .
READ MORE: Prince Wiliam and Princess Kate unfazed by efforts to ‘wound’ with family put first
The actual Coronation took place on May 6, 2023. (Image: Getty) The scene begins with Charles sitting down and William standing in front of him. Charles is dressed in his everyday clothes, a suit, but has the cloak over his shoulders.
William, too, is dressed in a suit. He says part of the vow, but doesn’t finish it, saving the entire pledge for the big day.
And, rather than actually touching the crown, he acts out the motion, and instead of kissing his father, he sort of tickles his face with his hand, but then does lean over to plant one on him.
